-- EU Aid Is Greece's `Last Chance,' Former Finance Minister Papantoniou Says
-- Rishaad Salamat
-- 2010-04-26T07:22:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-04-26/eu-aid-is-greece-s-last-chance-former-finance-minister-papantoniou-says.html

          
          
             Former Greek Finance Minister
Yannis Papantoniou said the European Union-International
Monetary Fund aid package for the country is its “last chance”
to avoid default.  
 Papantoniou also said in an interview with Bloomberg
Television in Athens today that the country needs “‘very great
reforms’’ on ‘‘both on fiscal side and competitive side’’ and
that the government has the will to implement them.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
Rishaad Salamat in London at 
 rishaad@bloomberg.net   
          
          


  
     
       
     
           
                           
                 
                 
                                       
                                   
               
                        
           
                           April 26 (Bloomberg) -- Yannis Papantoniou, a former Greek finance minister, talks with Bloomberg's Rishaad Salamat about measures to liberalize the Greek economy and stimulate growth.
     Papantoniou speaks from Athens. (Source: Bloomberg)
  
                           

     
